<HEADLINE>
<P>
THEODORE STRAVINSKY; ARTIST KNOWN FOR CHURCH WINDOWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Russian-born artist Theodore Stravinsky, 82, the eldest son of composer Igor 
Stravinsky. Born in 1907 in St. Petersburg, now Leningrad, Stravinsky spent 
most of his life in Morges, on the shores of Lake Geneva, and made his name 
painting stained glass windows in Swiss, French and Dutch churches. He wrote 
several art books and was made a commander of St. Gregori Magni by Pope Paul VI 
in 1977 for services to the Roman Catholic Church. His father died in 1971. In 
Geneva on Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
