<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIRE AT HAMBURG REFINERY KILLS ONE; DAMAGE HEAVY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HAMBURG, West Germany 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A major explosion and fire at a Shell oil refinery Thursday killed at least one 
worker, injured another and caused millions of dollars in damage, a fire 
brigade spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Firefighters battled the blaze at the Shell refinery in an industrial port 
section of Hamburg for more than eight hours. At times, the flames were more 
than 300 feet high, the firefighters said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
