<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MOTHER CHARGED IN 2ND CHILD DROWNING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A mother charged with a misdemeanor in California four years ago after her 
daughter drowned in a pool has been arrested in Pensacola, Fla., after the 
drowning of a second child, police said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Linda Key, 31, of Pomona, was arrested Wednesday and released on $15,000 bond 
after being charged with felony child neglect in the death this week of her 
2-year-old son, David. 
</P>
<P>
Key's lawyer, Bob Heath Jr. of Pensacola, said Key, who is in town visiting her 
mother, is scheduled to be arraigned June 8. He said his client plans to plead 
not guilty. 
</P>
<P>
David Key was playing in the back yard of his grandmother's home Saturday and 
threw a ball over a fence, according to the warrant. Key said that when she 
returned from retrieving the ball, she could not find her son. 
</P>
<P>
When she decided to go for a swim about 15 minutes later, she found the child 
face down in the pool. The boy was taken by helicopter to a hospital and died 
Monday. 
</P>
<P>
On Jan. 9, 1985, Key's 2-year-old daughter, Laura Elizabeth Key, died in Lake 
Elsinore, Calif. 
</P>
<P>
Heath said that Key faced a misdemeanor count in that case, although he was 
unsure of the precise charge. 
</P>
</TEXT>
