<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 26-YEAR TERM GIVEN IN GANG EXECUTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A gang member was sentenced Thursday to 26 years to life in state prison for 
murdering a man with a shotgun blast fired at point-blank range in the mistaken 
belief he was a member of a rival gang. 
</P>
<P>
Noe Alvarez, 18, convicted of first-degree murder Jan. 31, was sentenced in 
Compton Superior Court in the death of Henry Sao, 25. 
</P>
<P>
The district attorney's office said Sao was murdered Nov. 26, 1987, after he 
went to a beer party thrown by Alvarez and other members of his gang. 
</P>
<P>
Sao knew one of the people at the party, but was not a gang member. 
</P>
<P>
Members of Alvarez's gang accused Sao of being a rival gang member, then got 
him drunk and took him to the rear of a nearby liquor store. There they killed 
him with a single shotgun blast to the side of his head. 
</P>
</TEXT>
