<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN ACCUSED OF TAKING GUN INTO COURTHOUSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 27-year-old Pacoima man was arrested Thursday morning at the door of the San 
Fernando Courthouse after he tried to bring a loaded gun into the building, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Pedro Martinez Ortiz was carrying a .357 magnum wrapped in a black leather 
purse when he tried to enter the courthouse about 9:45 a.m. It is a felony to 
bring a loaded weapon into a courthouse. 
</P>
<P>
Deputy Marshal Jimmy Garcia, who was conducting routine security checks at the 
front door, discovered the weapon when Ortiz allowed him to look in the 
handbag. 
</P>
<P>
When Garcia discovered the gun, Ortiz denied any knowledge of the weapon. He 
said the purse belonged to a female friend who was waiting in court for another 
friend's arraignment. 
</P>
<P>
A police check revealed that the weapon had been stolen. Ortiz will be charged 
with carrying a concealed weapon and possession of stolen property. He faces a 
maximum sentence of five years. 
</P>
<P>
Ortiz was booked into the San Fernando Police Department and bail was set at 
$1,500. 
</P>
