<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TCS Enterprises: Net income rose by 123% to $533,000 for the second quarter 
ended March 31, up from $239,000 during the like quarter a year ago, the San 
Diego firm reported. Net income rose by 55%, to $538,000, for the six-month 
period ended March 31, up from $347,000 a year earlier. Revenue figures for the 
quarter and six-month periods were not available Thursday, a company 
spokeswoman said. 
</P>
