<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Advanced Marketing Services: The San Diego-based supplier of books to discount 
warehouse chains, including Price Club, reported fourth-quarter net income of 
$565,000 on sales of $26.3 million, up from a profit of $551,000 on sales of 
$24.1 million over the same quarter the previous year. 
</P>
<P>
For the fiscal year ended March 31, the company reported a profit of $5.1 
million on sales of $155.6 million, up from a profit of $3.6 million on sales 
of $110 million for the previous fiscal year. 
</P>
