<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Macy Says Units Not for Sale: The chairman of R. H. Macy &amp; Co. said the 
retailer -- which owns the Bullocks and I. Magnin chains -- feels its financial 
footing is secure since it went private in 1986 and it doesn't intend to divest 
any department store divisions. Edward S. Finkelstein said there have been 
persistent rumors that Macy's might be planning to sell off some assets to 
reduce its debt. There were also reports that Limited Inc., the nation's 
leading specialty apparel retailer, had preliminary talks about an investment 
in Macy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
DIVESTMENT; DEPARTMENT STORES; R H MACY &amp; CO INC 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA051989-0077 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 59071 </DOCID>
