HONOLULU INVESTOR HOLDS 7.9% STAKE IN CHANTAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Honolulu investor Garner Anthony said he acquired a 7.9% stake in Chantal 
Pharmaceutical Corp. for investment. 
</P>
<P>
In a Securities and Exchange Commission filing, Anthony said he holds 1.17 
million shares of Chantal, including 727,723 shares he bought from the company 
May 2 for $2 million. 
</P>
<P>
The stake also includes 415,000 shares purchased between March 13 and May 15 
for about 1.3 million. 
</P>
<P>
Chantal is a Los Angeles skin care products manufacturer. 
</P>
