<P>
91 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and international 
news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MTV Networks announced plans Thursday to launch a new basic cable television 
channel exclusively featuring comedy programming. The new channel, in 
development for the past 18 months, will be called "HA" TV Comedy Network. In 
addition to producing original programming, "HA" TV Comedy Network will acquire 
shows and movies from existing television and film libraries and will have 
access to comedy programs distributed by its parent company, Viacom. Launch 
date is early 1990. Cable giants HBO and Ted Turner also are planning comedy 
channels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
