<HEADLINE>
<P>
BEST BITES; 
</P>
<P>
A CHANCE TO EAT A MEAL FIT FOR A PERSIAN KING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RUTH REICHL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Eggplant with fried walnuts and caraway. . . . Goat cheese, olives and herbs 
rolled up in flat bread. . . . Roasted quail with a salad of cucumbers, sour 
grape juice, cilantro and mint. . . . Leg of lamb, marinated in onion juice and 
saffron and served with apricots and rice pilaf. . . . Pistachio custard with 
fresh peaches wrapped in filo pastry. 
</P>
<P>
Ancient Persian feasts are not normal restaurant fare in this part of the 
world, but this Sunday will be an exception. Gilliland's, 2424 Main St., Santa 
Monica, (213) 392-3901, will be serving the meal along with six different wines 
from Stonegate. The evening begins at 6 with a cooking demonstration, includes 
comments by an expert on ancient Persian food, and costs $55 per person.RUTH 
REICHL 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Restaurant Review 
</P>
