FOUNTAIN VALLEY'S GRAHAM LOSES IN NCAA DOUBLES FINAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Stanford's Debbie Graham, from Fountain Valley, and Sandra Birch were defeated 
by Mississippi State's Jackie Holden and Claire Pollard, 6-3, 7-6 (7-5), in the 
doubles final of the National Collegiate Athletic Assn. women's tennis 
championships at Gainesville, Fla., Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Birch won the individual championship by defeating Southern Methodist's 
Jennifer Santrock, 6-3, 6-3. 
</P>
<P>
Graham and Birch helped top-ranked Stanford win its fourth consecutive NCAA 
team championship Sunday. 
