<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE PREPS; 
</P>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION SOFTBALL PLAYOFFS; 
</P>
<P>
3 -- A; 
</P>
<P>
ROUSH PITCHES 1-HITTER; SAN CLEMENTE WINS, 1-0 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AL PRESTON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kathy Johnson doubled home the winning run in the bottom of the ninth inning 
Thursday to give San Clemente High School a 1-0 victory over University in a 
Southern Section 3-A first-round girls' softball playoff game at San Clemente. 
</P>
<P>
Johnson's game-winning hit supported the one-hit pitching of Tara Roush (9-6), 
who struck out eight, to pick up the victory that advances San Clemente (12-13) 
to Tuesday's second-round game against West Torrance, a 1-0 winner over Laguna 
Hills Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
University sophomore Shareen Patton (11-7) retired the first 17 batters she 
faced before Kim Denyer ruined her perfect-game bid by lining a single to 
right. 
</P>
<P>
"She just threw the ball right up the middle and it was ready for me to hit 
it," said Denyer, who was 0 for 25 in South Coast League play. 
</P>
<P>
Patton, who retired the next eight batters after Denyer was caught stealing to 
end the sixth, also yielded a single to Denyer with two outs in the ninth. 
Denyer, who stole second, came around to score when Johnson slammed a 2-2 pitch 
through the right-center field gap for the game-winning double. 
</P>
<P>
University (15-9), which played without its leading hitter, freshman Thea 
Curtis (flu), got its only hit off Roush in the top of the first on Lakita 
Johnson's two-out single. After that, the Trojans didn't have another 
base-runner until Roush walked Lisa Anthony with two outs in the seventh. 
</P>
<P>
In other 3-A softball: 
</P>
<P>
El Toro 3, Tustin 1 -- Junior Paige Lauby (13-7) pitched a one-hitter, striking 
out seven and walking none, to lead El Toro (13-8) at Tustin (17-8). Jaime 
Smith had two hits, scored a run and drove in a run for El Toro, which will 
play Montclair (22-4) in a quarterfinal game Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine 3, Mayfair 0 -- The host Vaqueros (19-7) scored three unearned runs in 
the third inning to beat Mayfair (15-10). Jennifer Brundage pitched a 
three-hitter, struck out six, walked one, and also went two for three with a 
run scored for Irvine, which will play Saddleback (24-4) Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Mission Viejo 4, South Torrance 1 -- Mission Viejo, an at-large team from the 
South Coast League, upset host South Torrance (14-5), the winner of the Ocean 
League. Erin Fitzgerald (9-4) pitched four-hitter and Michele Daugherty hit a 
two-run home run for the Diablos (15-8), who will play top-seeded La Mirada 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Saddleback 2, Woodbridge 0 (10 innings) -- Desi Abrego pitched a five-hitter 
with nine strikeouts and no walks for visiting Saddleback (24-4). The 
Roadrunners scored twice in the 10th on a bases-loaded dropped third strikeout 
with two outs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
