<HEADLINE>
<P>
OWNERS OF MID-SIZE O.C. FIRMS WELL PAID 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES S. GRANELLI, Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Owners of private, mid-size businesses in Orange County are the best paid in 
the state and rank among the best paid in the nation, according to a study by 
the Geneva Cos. in Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
In a nationwide study of 2,500 private companies with sales of $1 million to 
$100 million, Geneva found that the median compensation for business owners in 
Orange County was $224,000 a year over the past 2 years. Nationwide, that pay 
was $151,000 a year. 
</P>
<P>
The Orange County median compensation ranked eighth on a list of 80 
metropolitan areas nationwide. It was the highest in California, far surpassing 
Stockton, the next highest metropolitan area in the state listed. Stockton 
ranked 21st with a median pay of $193,000. 
</P>
<P>
"On average, the business owners are paying themselves 78% in direct salary and 
the remaining 22% in such indirect compensation as club memberships and 
personal financial planning expenses," said Charles B. Tillson, president of 
Geneva's international financial services division. 
</P>
<P>
Geneva, one of the nation's most active mergers and acquisitions firms, said 
the national median increased about 13% from the median $131,000 recorded in 
Geneva's 1986 survey. 
</P>
<P>
The median is the point at which half the salaries are higher and half are 
lower. 
</P>
<P>
Other California metropolitan areas on the list were Los Angeles (22nd), San 
Francisco (32nd), San Diego (39th), Bakersfield (58th), Sacramento (64th), Palm 
Springs (69th), San Bernardino (76th) and Santa Barbara (80th). 
</P>
<P>
</P>
