<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD; 
</P>
<P>
ALL AMERICANS URGED TO QUIT BEIRUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BEIRUT 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The U.S. Embassy said today all Americans remaining should leave Lebanon, and 
the leading Beirut newspaper predicted a Syrian assault on the Christian 
enclave defended by Gen. Michel Aoun's Christian army units. 
</P>
<P>
An official at the embassy said there are "several hundred Americans in 
Lebanon, most of them dual nationals." He would not be more specific. The 
embassy said in a statement that it is "not in a position to arrange 
transportation of citizens from Lebanon" but that Americans are "strongly 
advised to depart Lebanon immediately . . . because of the threat posed by the 
security situation." 
</P>
