<P>
13 FINED FOR DODGING CYCLE RACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ROME 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Thirteen top motorcycle riders, including five Americans, were fined $1,150 
each for boycotting the 500-cc race of the Italian motorcycling Grand Prix at 
Misano Adriatico last Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The Italian Motorcycling Federation said today that the fines were levied by an 
international jury and that the International Federation has been notified of 
the action. 
</P>
<P>
World champion Eddie Lawson and fellow Americans Kevin Schwantz, Freddie 
Spencer, Fred Merkel and Wayne Rainey were among the riders who refused to 
start in the race. They claimed that the Santa Monica track was left too 
slippery and dangerous after a sudden rainstorm. 
</P>
